wikipedia_page.main: Ella Briggs (née Baumfeld; 5 March 1880 – 20 June 1977) was an Austrian architect.

response: * Ella Briggs (née Baumfeld) (5 March 1880, Vienna, Austria-Hungary–20 June 1977, London, United Kingdom), was an Austrian and English architect who became the first female member of the Österreichischer Ingenieur- und Architekten-Verein (Austrian Engineers and Architects Association).
